\section{Panels accompanying the organ oratorio}
\label{sec:panels}

The performance was accompanied by a projection on two panels: The first displayed the text of the \emph{Book of Revelation} in New Testament Greek and an English translation, and the second displayed illustrations by Duane Bibby.\footnote{Duane Bibby's illustrations also appear in \emph{Fantasia Apocalyptica Illustrated}~\cite{knuth2018fantasia}, available on \href{https://www.amazon.com/Fantasia-Apocalyptica-Illustrated-Donald-Knuth/dp/1684000440}{Amazon} and elsewhere.}

In the video recording, we enhanced the panels as follows:
\begin{enumerate}
\item We added a Czech translation of the Book of Revelation to the text panel.
\item We increased the resolution of Duane Bibby's illustrations.
\item We added animations to transitions between text and illustrations on the first two panels.
\item Tom\'{a}\v{s} Szaniszlo prepared a third panel displaying organ sheet music.
\end{enumerate}

This section describes the preparation of the panels used in the video recording.

\input images/screen2-texts

\subsection{Trilingual text of \emph{Revelation}}
For the Greek and English text, we used a \acro{PDF} document from the Canadian premiere, which displays the Greek text on a light yellow background and the English text on a blue background; see Figure~\ref{fig:screen2-texts-greek-and-english-original}.

To match the top two colors of the Czech tricolor, we first decompressed the \acro{PDF} document using the free tool \acro{PDF}tk. We then used the \acro{POSIX} editor \texttt{sed} to modify the text and background colors so the English text appears on a red background; see Figure~\ref{fig:screen2-texts-greek-and-english-updated}.
\looseness=-1

For the Czech text, we used the Czech Ecumenical Translation with permission of the Czech Bible Society. Using \TeX, the Slabo font from Tiro Typeworks, and ImageMagick~\cite{imagemagick}, we created a document matching the Greek and English text and displaying the text on a blue background; see Figure~\ref{fig:screen2-texts-czech}.

\subsection{Illustrations by Duane Bibby}
We first extracted Duane Bibby's illustrations from the \acro{PDF} document using the free open-source tool pdfimages. We then increased their resolution using waifu2x, similarly to Figure~\ref{fig:waifu2x}.

