\section{Final video assembly}
\label{sec:final-video-assembly}

We combined the panel videos as shown in Figure~\ref{fig:montage-diagram}:

\begingroup
\small
\begin{verbatim}
$ ffmpeg -f lavfi -i color=c=white:s=3840x2160\
>                           :rate=50 \
>        -i input-greek-and-english-text.mp4 \
>        -i input-czech-text.mp4 \
>        -i input-illustrations.mp4 \
>        -i input-organ-sheet-music.mp4 \
> -filter_complex '
>   [0:v]null[background];
>   [1:v]null[greek-and-english-text];
>   [2:v]crop=1920:960:0:63[czech-text];
>   [3:v]pad=1920:1084:ow-iw/2:oh-ih/2'\
>          ':white[illustrations];
>   [4:v]crop=1344:1076:280:4,
>        pad=1920:1076:ow-iw/2:oh-ih/2'\
>          ':white[organ-scores];
>   [background][greek-and-english-text]
>     overlay=0:160[m1];
>   [m1][czech-text]overlay=0:1360[m2];
>   [m2][organ-scores]overlay=1920:1084[m3];
>   [m3][illustrations]overlay=1920[montage]' \
> -map '[montage]' -t 01:43:25 -r 50 panels.mp4
\end{verbatim}
\endgroup

We then prepended the opening speech and appended the closing to the panel video montage by concatenation~\cite{ffmpeg-concat}. Figure~\ref{fig:montage} shows the final video.

\section{Conclusion}
\label{sec:conclusion}

On December 18, 2019, the recording was screened in lecture hall \acro{D3} at \acro{FI~MU}; see Figure~\ref{fig:screening}.

Before the screening, Tom\'{a}\v{s} Szaniszlo played a digitized version of the music accompanying the verse~2:1 of \emph{Revelation} through piezoelectric speakers in a student computer room at \acro{FI~MU}. He also displayed a message inviting students to the screening. The first author, dressed as John the Apostle, then led the surprised students to the lecture hall.

The video was \href{https://youtu.be/wk7dEKMPP68}{published on the \acro{FI~MU} YouTube channel}~\cite{fimu2020english} on January 1, 2020.

